
[1]tranquilize

   TRAN'QUILIZE, v.t. To quiet; to allay when agitated; to compose; to
   make calm and peaceful; as, to tranquilize a state disturbed by
   factions or civil commotions; to tranquilize the mind.

   Religion haunts the imagination of the sinner, instead of tranquilizing
   his heart.
